frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with the sounds produced by animate entities by means of their vocal tracts.
This frame is  concerned with the percepts that vibrations which travel through the air or another medium produce in hearing organs.
A Communicator (whose Location may be indicated) directs a Communication to an Addressee at a particular Address.
An Agent moves Goods (or some other useful item) from an Exporting_area, across a boundary or border to a different area, the Importing_area.
A Producer produces a Product from a Resource for commercial purposes. '
An Author creates a Text, either written, such as a letter, or spoken, such as a speech,  that contains meaningful linguistic tokens, and may have a particular Addressee in mind.
frameExamples: He woke up because of the <t>cries</t> of the crows outside.
I awoke to the <t>clash</t> of a jackhammer on concrete.
Disgruntled voters <t>phoned</t> Congressman Neil at his Washington residence with complaints about the recent increases in corporate welfare.
Cooperating was an old term used by the Customs service to describe the illegal traffic of contrabandsold and <t>transhipped</t> from larger vessels into small local boats.
They <t>produced</t> only half of the units after an injunction to follow the environmental policy.
I <t>penned</t> a letter concerning racism to Congress.
listRoleDefinitions: An entity that is construed as a single point source emitting sound.

The location at which sound is produced. This role differs from <fen>Location_of_sound_source</fen> in that it does not highlight the sound's spreading from its source to the perceiver's location, which is usually indicated by the preposition 'from'.
An entity that is construed as a single point source emitting sound.

The location at which sound is produced. This role differs from Location_of_sound_source in that it does not highlight the sound's spreading from its source to the perceiver's location, which is usually indicated by the preposition 'from'.
The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a message to another person.
The person that receives the message from the <fen>Communicator</fen>.
This role is used for a (metaphorical) place in a system of communication where <fen>Communicator</fen>s and <fen>Addressee</fen>s can access the system.

The information that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wishes to impart to the <fen>Addressee</fen>, often to get a particular response. In this frame the <fen>Communication</fen> is not necessarily received by the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
This is the subject matter to which the message pertains. It is typically expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about'.
This role identifies the time when the Agent acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The items of value whose location is changing.
The role <fen>Importing_area</fen> is the place that the <fen>Goods</fen> end up as a result of motion.
The place where the <fen>Goods</fen> are initially, before the action.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The person or company that produces the Product.
The <fen>Product</fen> is produced by the <fen>Producer</fen>.
<fen>Factory</fen> identifies the particular plant where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
This Fe identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the product was produced.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
The <fen>Author</fen> produces a particular <fen>Text</fen>.
The entity which results from the act of writing or speaking.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the text is created.
Where the event takes place.

The hiss of snakes <fex>outside the tent</fex> was a constant source of worry.
He woke up because of the blare <fex>of a car horn</fex>.
There was a clatter of running feet <fex>in the street outside</fex>.
The company must be able to call <fex> potential customers</fex>.
Those machines were manufactured <fex>in the Miami plant</fex>.
Those leather shoes were made <fex>in Italy</fex>.
